JOSE NORMAN; CASTRO FOE 
Jose Norman, 83, a British-born musician and composer who, after marrying a 
Cuban woman and operating her family's coffee plantation, was forced out of 
Cuba by Fidel Castro. 
Norman came to Los Angeles in 1960 after living in Cuba's Oriente Province for 
11 years and became president of the Cuban Refugee Committee of Southern 
California. For the next several years, he spoke throughout the area 
encouraging the United States to drive out the Cuban leader. On Tuesday of 
cancer at his West Hollywood home. 
